In his place, Balotelli has done nothing so far to show why he has been afforded such adulation by his new supporters. He arrived with a big reputation - not all of it good, by any means - but it has been hard to see why there has been such noise around him.

Liverpool began this campaign aiming to build on the 84 points they collected last year and they needed a special talent to come and take over from Suarez. What they did not require was someone who only wants to turn it on when it suits.

Somehow Rodgers has to unlock Balotelli's ability - and resolve the issues that are threatening to dash their dreams.

 

